curcumin the active principle of turmeric is known to act as an antioxidant antimutagen and anticarcinogen in experimental animalsin the present study antimutagenic effects of turmeric were assessed in 16 chronic smokersit was observed that turmeric given in doses of 15 gday for 30 days significantly reduced the urinary excretion of mutagens in smokersin contrast in six nonsmokers who served as control there was no change in the urinary excretion of mutagens after 30 daysturmeric had no significant effect on serum aspartate aminotransferase and alanine aminotransferase blood glucose creatinine and lipid profilethese results indicate that dietary turmeric is an effective antimutagen and it may be useful in chemoprevention